Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired filtration. Low CO₂ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Despite glucosuria and ketonuria, blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, which is unusual and may suggest renal glycosuria or laboratory artifact. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended for further assessment and management.
